I completed the Phase 2.3.5 source-grounded prose review for the Layouts guide.

**Summary:**
The Layouts guide draft was well-written and accurate. All API references were verified against public headers, and code examples follow proper dali-ui idioms using `Dali::Ui::View`, typed setters, and fluent chaining.

**Change Made:**
One localized edit was required in the GridLayout > Auto-Sizing Grid Example section:
- Changed comment from "// Header spans both columns" to "// Header in the content column"
- The original comment was incorrect because the code uses `.SetColumn(1)` which places the header in column 1 only, not spanning both columns. To span columns, the code would need `.SetColumnSpan(2)`.

